or that you can hear a voice. They might say that you will receive a 
thought or stupor of thought. If we choose a specific direct-sense 
result, and we follow the steps necessary to receive it, and we actually
 receive that result, then we have completed the scientific method. This
 is all that is required for the scientific method to work.</p>
<p>This method of specifying the sense may not work for everyone though 
because individuals are the only tools for morality detection. This 
means that use of the scientific method to prove the existence of 
morality does not produce consistent results. Every individual receives 
and processes their own experiences in a different way. If the 
individual is essentially colorblind to that sensation, they may not 
