receive the result at all. There is too much variation in how the 
results of morality experiments can be received by individuals to be 
sure that the individuals received whatever sense was intended.<br>
If we had some sort of sensor that gathered a number in exactly the same
 way every time, we could be more certain that we were receiving the 
right result. Instead, we are making do with highly inconsistent 
detectors. We’re making do with our own subjective experience and the 
witness of other people’s subjective experiences. Even if we properly 
